title: 820-3115 light on charger, no fan spin

"PP3V3_SUS - 0V"
PM_SLP_SUS_L missing too?
Post PM_BATLOW_L, S5_PWRGD, PM_DSW_PWRGD, PCH_DSWVRMEN and the 4 RTC signals.

title: 820-3115 light on charger, no fan spin
message:
If you aren´t using a 85watt original adapter you won´t get the PM_BATLOW_L. That happened to me until I changed the PSU cable to a original 85 watt. And I understand that if you don´t have that voltage you wont be able to activate the PCH.
see if this can help you:
[URL unfurl="true"]https://www.it-tech.com.au/mac-q-a/pm-slp-s4-l-timing/[/URL]

message:
Just to confirm I got genuine 85W charger.
Tried three chargers and got same voltage on PM_BATLOW_L

title: 820-3115 light on charger, no fan spin
message:
"PM_SLP_SUS_L - 3.32V"
Then you MUST have 3V3_SUS too; check that again.
If not present, check for short and post Q7802/20 voltages.
